Interview One-Line Summary
==========================
When kubectl apply is executed, Kubernetes validates the manifest through the API Server, stores the desired state in etcd, schedules workloads to nodes, and kubelet creates and runs the containers using the container runtime.



Q) How does Kubernetes maintain the desired state?
Kubernetes maintains the desired state through controllers that continuously compare the desired configuration stored in etcd with the actual cluster state and automatically reconcile any differences.


